75
00:08:20,819 --> 00:08:22,588
She puts her boyfriend...

76
00:08:22,588 --> 00:08:26,008
and her dog before me.

77
00:08:26,359 --> 00:08:28,658
I'm not interested in men.

78
00:08:28,658 --> 00:08:30,479
I know they're all the same.

79
00:08:31,468 --> 00:08:33,398
All I have left is work,

80
00:08:33,398 --> 00:08:35,689
but it's starting to get boring too.

81
00:08:39,769 --> 00:08:41,189
Comfort me.

82
00:08:42,509 --> 00:08:44,628
Even better if you have a solution.

83
00:08:45,748 --> 00:08:47,428
You want a solution?

84
00:08:47,779 --> 00:08:48,898
Yes.

85
00:08:49,748 --> 00:08:51,498
Say something.

86
00:09:06,738 --> 00:09:10,489
How will you win the viewers over when you can't even get to me?

87
00:09:20,578 --> 00:09:22,028
(Rejected, Revised)

88
00:09:24,988 --> 00:09:26,339
(Monthly Schedule)

89
00:09:30,088 --> 00:09:31,378
Then you should...

90
00:09:38,698 --> 00:09:39,849
just quit.

91
00:09:43,169 --> 00:09:47,028
There is nothing worse than keeping a boring job.

92
00:09:49,478 --> 00:09:51,798
Some of my customers...

93
00:09:52,208 --> 00:09:55,599
always talk about quitting their jobs.

94
00:09:56,519 --> 00:09:57,998
They are frustrated...

95
00:09:58,218 --> 00:10:00,609
at even the thought of going to work in the morning.

96
00:10:02,059 --> 00:10:03,469
It might be the right choice...

97
00:10:04,458 --> 00:10:06,508
for them to quit...

98
00:10:09,259 --> 00:10:11,479
rather than waste their lives like that.

99
00:10:12,529 --> 00:10:14,089
It's such a waste.

100
00:10:24,309 --> 00:10:25,798
But interestingly,

101
00:10:27,549 --> 00:10:30,439
some of those who say their work is boring...

102
00:10:31,919 --> 00:10:35,008
are workaholics.

103
00:10:38,358 --> 00:10:39,628
When they are on vacation,

104
00:10:39,628 --> 00:10:41,949
they pack their laptops instead of swimsuits.

105
00:10:42,498 --> 00:10:45,748
Nature doesn't impress them at all.

106
00:10:47,039 --> 00:10:49,689
People like that always return...

107
00:10:50,909 --> 00:10:53,018
to what they love.

108
00:10:53,909 --> 00:10:55,158
So,

109
00:10:56,179 --> 00:10:57,398
you should try quitting.

110
00:10:58,378 --> 00:11:00,229
If you want to figure out what matters to you,

111
00:11:00,978 --> 00:11:04,699
losing it first is an option.

112
00:12:11,689 --> 00:12:14,668
I ran into you earlier, right?

113
00:12:15,488 --> 00:12:17,979
Are you okay?

114
00:12:26,098 --> 00:12:29,288
I'm sure you're here since you're okay.

115
00:12:37,049 --> 00:12:40,369
I stand out because of my flashy outfit, right?

116
00:12:44,488 --> 00:12:46,718
I can explain.

117
00:12:46,718 --> 00:12:48,369
There's a thin line...

118
00:12:49,289 --> 00:12:50,809
between fashion and costumes.

119
00:12:54,358 --> 00:12:56,648
If it's too much, you'll look ridiculous.

120
00:12:59,029 --> 00:13:00,079
Excuse me.

121
00:13:01,139 --> 00:13:04,619
Are you saying that I look ridiculous?

122
00:13:09,009 --> 00:13:10,798
I didn't expect this, Ah Jin.

123
00:13:11,549 --> 00:13:13,729
That wasn't bad for someone you found within a day.

124
00:13:15,978 --> 00:13:18,498
Show me what you had in mind.

125
00:13:24,929 --> 00:13:26,579
Really?

126
00:13:28,429 --> 00:13:29,479
Yes.

127
00:13:35,498 --> 00:13:37,459
Thank you.

128
00:13:38,509 --> 00:13:40,158
Seriously...

129
00:13:40,978 --> 00:13:43,829
Thank you so much for giving me this chance.

130
00:13:44,208 --> 00:13:47,199
I'll make a great show by all means.

131
00:13:49,718 --> 00:13:50,768
Thank you.

132
00:13:52,848 --> 00:13:53,969
Thank you so much.

133
00:13:55,588 --> 00:13:56,709
Okay.

134
00:14:01,159 --> 00:14:02,878
Thank you, Ms. Cha!

135
00:14:05,098 --> 00:14:06,918
Isn't that what you've been thinking too?

136
00:14:07,899 --> 00:14:10,069
- Pardon? - You've been self-conscious...

137
00:14:10,069 --> 00:14:11,658
the whole time.

138
00:14:12,769 --> 00:14:15,628
As if you're wearing someone else's clothes.

139
00:14:19,448 --> 00:14:21,998
There's also a thin line between over-the-top and fancy.

140
00:14:23,419 --> 00:14:24,869
It's all about balance.

141
00:14:31,488 --> 00:14:33,408
Mr. Kang, are you ready?

142
00:14:39,098 --> 00:14:40,148
See you.

143
00:15:02,289 --> 00:15:03,339
Why...

144
00:15:04,328 --> 00:15:05,538
are you looking at me like that?

145
00:15:07,529 --> 00:15:08,579
Well...

146
00:15:11,598 --> 00:15:14,349
How did you persuade Ms. Cha?

147
00:15:18,569 --> 00:15:21,028
Did I pass?

148
00:15:21,978 --> 00:15:23,528
She said I can make a pilot.

149
00:15:23,679 --> 00:15:26,409
- Really? - Thank you so much.

150
00:15:26,409 --> 00:15:27,798
Thank you.

151
00:15:28,578 --> 00:15:29,969
- Ms. Kim. - Yes?

152
00:15:30,179 --> 00:15:32,538
When can I...

153
00:15:34,618 --> 00:15:36,709
When can I get paid?

154
00:15:41,998 --> 00:15:43,048
When can you get paid?

155
00:15:53,468 --> 00:15:55,628
I did it! This is unbelievable.

156
00:16:01,279 --> 00:16:02,329
My goodness.

157
00:16:09,189 --> 00:16:10,638
Sung Eun!

158
00:16:10,659 --> 00:16:12,029
- Sung Eun! - Hey!

159
00:16:12,029 --> 00:16:14,958
- Congratulations. - Thank you.

160
00:16:14,958 --> 00:16:16,958
- Can you make the show now? - I can't believe this.

161
00:16:16,958 --> 00:16:19,098
- Really? - Can you believe this?

162
00:16:19,098 --> 00:16:21,299
Great job, Ah Jin.

163
00:16:21,299 --> 00:16:22,968
Hey.

164
00:16:22,968 --> 00:16:25,439
By the way, do you know the chef?

165
00:16:25,439 --> 00:16:26,658
It looked like it.

166
00:16:27,378 --> 00:16:30,559
He runs Bistro I often go to.

167
00:16:31,078 --> 00:16:32,549
It's him?

168
00:16:32,549 --> 00:16:34,279
Then you could have cast him from the beginning.

169
00:16:34,279 --> 00:16:36,428
Why did you go through all that trouble?

170
00:16:37,319 --> 00:16:38,599
I had no idea.

171
00:16:39,049 --> 00:16:40,099
How come?

172
00:16:40,819 --> 00:16:42,869
You go there all the time.

173
00:16:44,189 --> 00:16:45,309
I know.

174
00:16:45,988 --> 00:16:49,008
Then again, how would you know if he doesn't tell you?

175
00:16:51,468 --> 00:16:55,489
Hey, what's with that disappointed look on your face?

176
00:16:56,738 --> 00:16:58,208
It's not like that.

177
00:16:58,208 --> 00:16:59,868
Don't tell me...

178
00:16:59,868 --> 00:17:02,089
you asked him out and he turned you down.

179
00:17:03,978 --> 00:17:05,978
Don't be ridiculous.

180
00:17:05,978 --> 00:17:09,449
By the way, I don't have enough budget.

181
00:17:09,449 --> 00:17:10,738
What should I do?

182
00:17:11,219 --> 00:17:14,408
Let Director Kim Ah Jin take care of it tomorrow.

183
00:17:15,118 --> 00:17:16,938
- Tomorrow? - Today...

184
00:17:17,088 --> 00:17:19,328
is your last day as an assistant director.

185
00:17:19,328 --> 00:17:21,259
We should drink.

186
00:17:21,259 --> 00:17:22,259
Buy me a drink.

187
00:17:22,259 --> 00:17:23,699
- You're a director now. - Okay.

188
00:17:23,699 --> 00:17:25,969
Ah Jin, you finally did it.

189
00:17:25,969 --> 00:17:27,438
Congratulations.

190
00:17:27,438 --> 00:17:28,988
Shouldn't we go for a drink?

191
00:17:29,338 --> 00:17:31,888
Where should we go?

192
00:17:32,969 --> 00:17:34,408
- What's with him? - No idea.

193
00:17:34,408 --> 00:17:37,979
Right. Guys, the whole hallway...

194
00:17:37,979 --> 00:17:39,709
smells like fried food.

195
00:17:39,709 --> 00:17:42,279
How about we go for some makgeolli?

196
00:17:42,279 --> 00:17:43,668
Makgeolli sounds amazing.

197
00:17:46,848 --> 00:17:48,269
- Let's go. - Okay.

198
00:17:48,719 --> 00:17:52,339
Kwang Su, your styling has been pretty good so far.

199
00:17:53,459 --> 00:17:55,549
It's sophisticated, and I like the way you use accessories.

200
00:17:55,799 --> 00:17:57,009
It's always controlled.

201
00:17:57,598 --> 00:17:58,648
Dad.

202
00:17:59,398 --> 00:18:02,448
- He's my favorite designer. - I wanted to be bold this time.

203
00:18:03,138 --> 00:18:04,188
Really?

204
00:18:04,638 --> 00:18:07,728
It's my dream to walk the runway in his clothes.

205
00:18:08,779 --> 00:18:10,829
- I'm here. - Hi.

206
00:18:13,378 --> 00:18:14,569
How are you feeling?

207
00:18:14,979 --> 00:18:16,269
I'm okay.

208
00:18:16,979 --> 00:18:19,299
You didn't have to come. What about Bistro?

209
00:18:21,688 --> 00:18:22,938
In Deok is there.

210
00:18:25,188 --> 00:18:26,579
- Did you eat? - Hold on.

211
00:18:26,959 --> 00:18:28,378
I don't want to miss this part.

212
00:18:34,239 --> 00:18:35,418
It's that jerk.

213
00:18:35,638 --> 00:18:36,988
- Do you have anything to add? - Hey.

214
00:18:37,739 --> 00:18:39,039
Is he famous?

215
00:18:39,039 --> 00:18:40,089
Yes.

216
00:18:40,338 --> 00:18:41,589
How famous?

217
00:18:42,078 --> 00:18:45,529
Famous enough to host a show like that alone at his age.

218
00:18:45,809 --> 00:18:47,198
He's a huge star.

219
00:18:48,078 --> 00:18:49,128
Please go back.

220
00:18:51,918 --> 00:18:53,269
Gosh.

221
00:19:08,239 --> 00:19:11,119
Thanks for taking good care of Dad.

222
00:19:14,209 --> 00:19:16,859
Jin Sung, make some food for me.

223
00:19:17,848 --> 00:19:19,809
At this hour? Are you hungry?

224
00:19:19,809 --> 00:19:22,029
Yes, I'm starving.

225
00:19:22,519 --> 00:19:23,628
Gosh.

226
00:19:25,819 --> 00:19:27,559
All right. I'll go change first.

227
00:19:27,559 --> 00:19:28,708
Yes!

228
00:20:30,019 --> 00:20:31,599
What is he doing?

229
00:20:37,158 --> 00:20:38,208
Come here.

230
00:20:42,828 --> 00:20:45,049
Wow, that looks delicious.

231
00:20:47,539 --> 00:20:49,619
Jin Sung, how do I look?

232
00:20:50,098 --> 00:20:51,359
I have an audition soon.

233
00:20:51,438 --> 00:20:52,888
That's why I bought this.

234
00:20:53,908 --> 00:20:55,029
Are you auditioning for a nightclub?

235
00:20:55,678 --> 00:20:56,958
What do I know?

236
00:20:57,338 --> 00:20:59,759
You're right. You know nothing about fashion.

237
00:21:05,348 --> 00:21:06,799
- Jin Woo. - Yes?

238
00:21:08,489 --> 00:21:09,539
How...

239
00:21:10,088 --> 00:21:12,839
did you know you were special?

240
00:21:14,029 --> 00:21:16,127
You're going to nag me, aren't you?

241
00:21:16,128 --> 00:21:18,749
I'm not. I'm just curious.

242
00:21:20,628 --> 00:21:22,589
I just found out naturally.

243
00:21:23,098 --> 00:21:25,158
I realized what I liked,

244
00:21:26,209 --> 00:21:28,928
and it was different from what most people liked.

245
00:21:30,309 --> 00:21:31,428
Can you tell...

246
00:21:32,408 --> 00:21:33,898
just by looking...

247
00:21:34,549 --> 00:21:36,269
whether a person is gay or not?

248
00:21:38,648 --> 00:21:40,539
Not if that person hides it well.

249
00:21:41,519 --> 00:21:43,388
Take Tae Sik, the pride of our neighborhood, for example.

250
00:21:43,388 --> 00:21:45,839
No one knew before he came out himself.

251
00:21:47,658 --> 00:21:49,249
No one knew?

252
00:21:51,398 --> 00:21:54,239
You know passion is never enough.

253
00:21:54,239 --> 00:21:57,019
She'll be out of here once her contract is up. Am I wrong?

254
00:21:57,668 --> 00:21:58,958
Let's face it.

255
00:21:59,509 --> 00:22:02,479
Think of Park Sin Ho, Kim Hye Jeong, and Ko Seung Ju.

256
00:22:02,479 --> 00:22:04,348
None of their contracts got extended.

257
00:22:04,348 --> 00:22:05,979
They can't even negotiate their salaries.

258
00:22:05,979 --> 00:22:08,099
They have no reason to stay here.

259
00:22:08,249 --> 00:22:10,279
Who knows "Sweet Munchies" will become a hit and she'll make it big?

260
00:22:10,279 --> 00:22:11,339
You never know.

261
00:22:11,989 --> 00:22:13,049
No way.

262
00:22:13,049 --> 00:22:15,539
There's no way that's going to happen.

263
00:22:16,358 --> 00:22:17,738
What about the assistant director?

264
00:22:18,029 --> 00:22:19,809
I don't need one.

265
00:22:20,328 --> 00:22:21,378
What do you mean?

266
00:22:21,898 --> 00:22:24,229
If No Jae Soo is going to be my assistant director,

267
00:22:24,229 --> 00:22:26,319
I'd rather not have any assistant director at all.

268
00:22:26,598 --> 00:22:29,699
He'll look down on me because I'm not a permanent employee,

269
00:22:29,699 --> 00:22:31,789
and he'll ruin the whole atmosphere.

270
00:22:32,138 --> 00:22:34,688
If you only want to work with people you like,

271
00:22:35,078 --> 00:22:36,658
start a club instead.

272
00:22:36,739 --> 00:22:38,779
You can't make a show alone.

273
00:22:38,779 --> 00:22:40,228
You always need other people.

274
00:22:40,979 --> 00:22:44,648
Still, I couldn't force him to work on this show if he doesn't want to.

275
00:22:44,648 --> 00:22:46,019
Make him want to.

276
00:22:46,019 --> 00:22:48,009
That's also a director's job.

277
00:22:50,118 --> 00:22:52,178
This is a jungle.

278
00:22:52,729 --> 00:22:54,858
